page.title: 13Plants
page.content: {In our area there many plants.}The most common plants are grasses, bracken, ling and bell heathers.{There {are also a lot of brambles and gorse {bushes.}In June we found the following flowering plants in one small area, dandilion, buttercups, cow parsley, wild roses, honey suckle, bell heather, dwarf gorse, creeping buttercup, meadow vetchling, meadow cranesbill, red dead nettle, toad-flax, clover, water figot, bagle, spotted medick, sorrel, sheperd's purse.{Much of the plant life has to {over come the eating habits of deer, {ponies and other wild animals.}Humans also rob the forest of plants.{Some of {the plants are poisonous to animals {and humans e.g. ragwort, foxglove {bracken. Stuart Austin 8.}Some times dense bushes keep the animals off and plants can grow in their protection.
